President Biden has announced his nominees for the AMTRAK Board of Directors. The nominees are David Capozzi, a retired federal senior executive; Anthony Coscia, current Chairman of the AMTRAK Board of Directors; Christopher Koos, Mayor of Normal, Illinois; Samuel Lathem, the first African-American President of Delaware State AFL-CIO; and Robin Wiessmann, Executive Director and CEO of the Pennsylvania Housing Finance Agency. Each nominee brings a unique set of experiences and expertise to the board.